piles\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T1.5** Verify `DownloadFileHandler` exists\n41:   - Check: Handler strips leading slash, validates path, detects MIME type\n42:   - Check: Handler sets Content-Disposition header, streams file\n43:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n44:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T1.6** Verify route registration in `pkg/picod/server.go`\n47:   - Check: `/api/files` POST → UploadFileHandler\n48:   - Check: `/api/files` GET → ListFilesHandler\n49:   - Check: `/api/files/*path` GET → DownloadFileHandler\n50:   - Verify: `grep -n \"api.*files\" pkg/picod/server.go`\n51:   - Independently verifiable: All three routes registered\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ### Phase 2: File Upload Handler Tests\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.1** Test multipart upload\n58:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart` exists and passes\n59:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n60:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file written\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T2.2** Test JSON Base64 upload\n63:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerJSON` exists and passes\n64:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n65:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, content decoded\n66: \n67: - [ ] **T2.3** Test invalid Base64 content\n68:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64` exists and passes\n69:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64 ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n70:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\"\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T2.4** Test path traversal detection\n73:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n74:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n75:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T2.5** Test invalid file mode (non-octal)\n78:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode` exists and passes\n79:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n80:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, uses default 0644\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T2.6** Test file mode > 0777\n83:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n84:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n85:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\"\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T2.7** Test parent directory creation\n88:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation` exists and passes\n89:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n90:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, parents created with 0755\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T2.8** Add test for multipart missing path\n93:   - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath`\n94:   - Input: multipart form without `path` field\n95:   - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n96:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n97:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T2.9** Add test for multipart missing file\n100:   - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile`\n101:   - Input: multipart form without `file` field\n102:   - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing file\"\n103:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n104:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Phase 3: File List Handler Tests\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.1** Test valid directory listing\n111:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory` exists and passes\n112:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n113:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, FileEntry array\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T3.2** Test missing path parameter\n116:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath` exists and passes\n117:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n118:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T3.3** Test path traversal detection\n121:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n122:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n123:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T3.4** Test non-existent directory\n126:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent` exists and passes\n127:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n128:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\"\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T3.5** Add test for empty directory\n131:   - Create: `TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory`\n132:   - Setup: Create empty directory in workspace\n133:   - Expected: HTTP 200, empty `files` array\n134:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n135:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Phase 4: File Download Handler Tests\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T4.1** Test existing file download\n142:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerExistingFile` exists and passes\n143:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerExistingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n144:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file content matches\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T4.2** Test leading slash stripped\n147:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerLeadingSlash` exists and passes\n148:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerLeadingSlash ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n149:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, resolved correctly\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T4.3** Test path traversal detection\n152:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n153:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n154:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.4** Test file not found\n157:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerNotFound` exists and passes\n158:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerNotFound ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n159:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 404, \"file not found\"\n160: \n161: - [ ] **T4.5** Test path is directory\n162:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerIsDirectory` exists and passes\n163:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerIsDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n164:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\"\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T4.6** Add test for MIME type detection (.json)\n167:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeJSON`\n168:   - Setup: Write `data.json` file\n169:   - Expected: HTTP 200, Content-Type: application/json\n170:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n171:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T4.7** Add test for unknown extension MIME type\n174:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown`\n175:   - Setup: Write `data.xyz` file\n176:   - Expected: HTTP 200, Content-Type: application/octet-stream\n177:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n178:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T4.8** Add test for symlink inside workspace\n181:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace`\n182:   - Setup: Create file, create symlink pointing to file within workspace\n183:   - Expected: HTTP 200, file content from symlink\n184:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n185:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Phase 5: File Mode Parsing Tests\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.1** Test empty mode returns default\n192:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeEmpty` exists and passes\n193:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeEmpty ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n194:   - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T5.2** Test invalid mode returns default\n197:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeInvalid` exists and passes\n198:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeInvalid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n199:   - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T5.3** Test mode > 0777 returns error\n202:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n203:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n204:   - Independently verifiable: Returns error \"invalid file mode\"\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T5.4** Test valid mode parsing\n207:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeValid` exists and passes\n208:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeValid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n209:   - Independently verifiable: Returns correct FileMode\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### Phase 6: Integration Tests\n214: \n215: - [ ] **T6.1** Test full file lifecycle\n216:   - Create: `TestFileLifecycle`\n217:   - Steps: Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content\n218:   - Verify: `go test -run TestFileLifecycle ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n219:   - Independently verifiable: All operations succeed, content matches\n220: \n221: - [ ] **T6.2** Test large file upload (near 32 MiB limit)\n222:   - Create: `TestUploadLargeFile`\n223:   - Setup: Generate file ~30 MiB\n224:   - Expected: HTTP 200, file written\n225:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadLargeFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n226:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T6.3** Test concurrent operations\n229:   - Create: `TestConcurrentFileOperations`\n230:   - Setup: Multiple upload/download requests in parallel\n231:   - Expected: All succeed without race conditions\n232:   - Verify: `go test -race -run TestConcurrentFileOperations ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n233:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes with race detector\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Phase 7: Validation and Linting\n238: \n239: - [ ] **T7.1** Run `go vet` on picod package\n240:   - Run: `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n241:   - Verify: No warnings\n242:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T7.2** Run `golangci-lint` on picod package\n245:   - Run: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n246:   - Verify: No errors\n247:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T7.3** Run all tests with race detector\n250:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n251:   - Verify: All tests pass\n252:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T7.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n255:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n256:   - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n257:   - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ### Phase 8: Binary Validation\n262: \n263: - [ ] **T8.1** Build picod binary\n264:   - Run: `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod/`\n265:   - Verify: Binary exists\n266:   - Independently verifiable: `ls picod`\n267: \n268: - [ ] **T8.2** Run binary with test public key\n269:   - Setup: Generate RSA key pair\n270:   - Setup: Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n271:   - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n272:   - Call: `/health` endpoint\n273:   - Expected: HTTP 200 response\n274:   - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T8.3** Test file upload via binary\n277:   - Setup: Server running with valid JWT\n278:   - Call: `POST /api/files` with JSON upload\n279:   - Expected: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n280:   - Independently verifiable: File created in workspace\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Acceptance Criteria\n285: \n286: - [ ] `pkg/picod/files.go` contains FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs\n287: - [ ] `parseFileMode` handles empty/invalid/valid/>0777 modes correctly\n288: - [ ] `UploadFileHandler` supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n289: - [ ] `UploadFileHandler` validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent directories\n290: - [ ] `ListFilesHandler` validates path, reads directory, returns FileEntry array\n291: - [ ] `DownloadFileHandler` validates path, detects MIME type, streams file\n292: - [ ] All three file routes registered in server.go\n293: - [ ] All file handler tests pass\n294: - [ ] Path traversal protection works for upload, list, download\n295: - [ ] File mode validation prevents setuid/setgid bits (max 0777)\n296: - [ ] Pass `go vet`\n297: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n298: - [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n299: - [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and handles file operations\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## File Changes Summary\n304: \n305: | File | Action | Lines Changed |\n306: |------|--------|---------------|\n307: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Existing | ~230 lines |\n308: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Existing | Routes at lines 71-73 |\n309: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Modify | +~60 lines (new tests) |\n310: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Existing | ~35 lines |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Implementation Notes\n315: \n316: - File upload supports both `multipart/form-data` and `application/json` (Base64 encoded)\n317: - Path sanitization via `sanitizePath` enforces workspace jail security\n318: - File mode parsing: `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` for octal, max 0777\n319: - MIME type detection: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`\n320: - Content-Disposition header: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n321: - Parent directories created with 0755 mode\n322: - Default file mode: 0644\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/files.go` structs exist\n  - Check: `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775863059838,"end":1775863059860}}}}
